1
00:00:37,070 --> 00:00:42,349
<i>In ancient times, the world was
ruled by gods and monsters.</i>

2
00:00:44,444 --> 00:00:47,448
<i>But it was the half-god Perseus,
my son...</i>

3
00:00:47,614 --> 00:00:51,323
<i>...who defeated the Kraken
and saved humanity.</i>

4
00:00:53,019 --> 00:00:57,263
<i>For his courage, I offered him
a place to rule at my side.</i>

5
00:00:58,725 --> 00:00:59,760
<i>But Perseus...</i>

6
00:00:59,926 --> 00:01:03,703
<i>strong-willed
and chose a different path</i>

7
00:01:03,863 --> 00:01:07,037
<i>He vowed to live as a man.</i>

8
00:01:08,768 --> 00:01:11,078
<i>Even when fate took his wife...</i>

9
00:01:11,237 --> 00:01:13,911
...he would not pray for help, from me...

10
00:01:14,541 --> 00:01:16,111
...or the other gods.

11
00:01:17,710 --> 00:01:20,714
<i>And now the time of the gods is ending.</i>

12
00:01:20,947 --> 00:01:25,157
<i>But the son of Zeus cannot hide
from his destiny forever.</i>

13
00:01:28,421 --> 00:01:29,900
New pull it in. Dc it again.

14
00:01:30,090 --> 00:01:33,003
Throw in the other one real quick.
Go on. I'll tie this off.

15
00:01:39,299 --> 00:01:40,573
Goad catch today, Dad.

16
00:01:42,969 --> 00:01:46,280
- Where'd you get that?
- I made it myself.

17
00:01:48,942 --> 00:01:51,946
You made it yourself? Heh.

18
00:01:52,512 --> 00:01:54,685
I want to be a good god
and do good things.

19
00:01:54,881 --> 00:01:57,828
There's no such thing as good gods.
Some of them are good.

20
00:01:57,984 --> 00:02:01,522
Ah. Helius, there's more to life
than gods and Titans.

21
00:02:02,489 --> 00:02:05,629
Hey, Clea. I have a confession to make.

22
00:02:06,126 --> 00:02:08,299
I, uh, needed him for chores
so he skipped studying.

23
00:02:09,529 --> 00:02:13,272
Now, you do a good jab, make me proud.

24
00:02:21,341 --> 00:02:23,321
{THUNDER RUMBLING}

25
00:02:36,156 --> 00:02:38,193
I know you're here.

26
00:02:45,999 --> 00:02:48,172
I visit him sometimes in his dreams.

27
00:02:48,334 --> 00:02:50,940
He's like his father. A strong-willed bay.

28
00:02:52,305 --> 00:02:53,511
You just passing through?

29
00:02:56,476 --> 00:02:57,819
Na.

30
00:02:58,978 --> 00:02:59,854
I need your help...

31
00:03:00,013 --> 00:03:01,083
...Perseus.

32
00:03:01,814 --> 00:03:04,385
You're the great god Zeus.
You don't need my help.

33
00:03:05,251 --> 00:03:07,527
There is a calamity coming.

34
00:03:07,687 --> 00:03:10,691
It will affect us all. Gods and men.

35
00:03:11,457 --> 00:03:14,404
- The humans may have stopped praying to us...
- With good reason.

36
00:03:14,561 --> 00:03:16,097
...but there are consequences.

37
00:03:17,163 --> 00:03:19,507
Without prayer, we gods lose our power.

38
00:03:19,666 --> 00:03:24,376
When our power leaves us,
all our work comes undone. All of it.

39
00:03:24,971 --> 00:03:26,712
{RUMBLING}

40
00:03:34,380 --> 00:03:36,758
The walls of Tartarus are falling.

41
00:03:37,183 --> 00:03:41,757
It is emptying all its demons onto the earth.
The first are already here.

42
00:03:42,689 --> 00:03:47,195
If our power diminishes much further,
we gods will became mortal.

43
00:03:47,360 --> 00:03:49,931
We will die and Kronos himself will escape.

44
00:03:50,730 --> 00:03:54,143
It will mean chaos. The end of the world.

45
00:03:54,500 --> 00:03:56,241
What am I meant to do?

46
00:03:58,137 --> 00:03:59,411
This is business for gods.

47
00:03:59,639 --> 00:04:01,585
We need all our children now.

48
00:04:02,108 --> 00:04:04,110
Perhaps, together...

49
00:04:04,277 --> 00:04:05,756
...we can remedy this.

50
00:04:05,912 --> 00:04:08,654
But we need every shred of power, Perseus.

51
00:04:11,584 --> 00:04:13,621
I will never leave my sun.

52
